Random Th*ts: But keep them Away. Far tf away. We talked about this on live the other day but it’s true. I really do not have the cups to fill up things that should already inherently be within people. Think about every person you know with terribly low self esteem now think about their relationships since y’all know this is the page where all SHIPS matter we’re not just talking about romantic ones but even platonic ones they’re in shambles, right? We as people are all faced with different insecurities and all of us have things to work on but having low self esteem breeds conflict and chaos. It invites a need for competition and competitive behavior that’s completely unnecessary. How are your relationships expected to be safe places when you’re constantly competing in them? I’ve seen it between, friends, partners, family members and it’s sad asf every time cause how does someone else feeling they’re great mean that you aren’t it doesn’t but somehow you projected that feeling of unworthiness because you already felt UNWORTHY. There’s nothing wrong with needing to do more work, there’s nothing wrong with feeling as though you have to be better but to carry that same energy into your SHIPS is the reason they’re failing. One thing I’ve noticed is that people with decent self esteem just move differently I always talk about L&D and that man never gaf about who, what, or where I was cause he knew I’d be omw back and just that level of certainty was assuring cause really where tf was I bout to go he knew he was on his job so I mean he knew that if I wandered I wasn’t going far and I didn’t. Idk I just don’t really wanna over explain myself due to other peoples insecurities with this 1HPY slowly approaching matter I don’t wanna explain myself at all.
